<%# ================================================================
    [06] FEATURES
    ================================================================ %>
<section class="comp-features section-padding" aria-label="Compiler features">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Built for Developers</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Everything you need to write, run, and debug code. Without leaving your browser.</p>

    <div class="comp-features-grid">
      <div class="comp-feature-card">
        <h3>Sandboxed Execution</h3>
        <p>Your code runs in an isolated container via the Piston execution engine. No risk to our servers, no risk to your data.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-feature-card">
        <h3>Lightning Fast</h3>
        <p>Results in seconds. LRU caching means repeated executions return instantly. Smart auto-retry on transient errors.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-feature-card">
        <h3>STDIN Support</h3>
        <p>Provide standard input for programs that read from stdin. Perfect for competitive programming and interactive programs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-feature-card">
        <h3>Syntax Highlighting</h3>
        <p>Full CodeMirror 5 integration with language-aware syntax highlighting, bracket matching, auto-indent, and code folding.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-feature-card">
        <h3>Rich Error Output</h3>
        <p>Compile errors, runtime errors, and stderr are all displayed clearly with color coding. Debug faster.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="comp-feature-card">
        <h3>Download and Auto-Save</h3>
        <p>Download your code as a properly-named file. Your code auto-saves to localStorage. Never lose your work on refresh.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<%# ================================================================
    [07] FAQ
    ================================================================ %>
<section class="comp-faq section-padding" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="comp-faq-list">
      <details class="comp-faq-item" open>
        <summary class="comp-faq-q">Is the online compiler free to use?</summary>
        <div class="comp-faq-a">
          <p>Yes, Value.Codes Online Compiler is completely free. No signup, no subscription, no hidden costs. You can run code in all 19 supported languages without creating an account.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="comp-faq-item">
        <summary class="comp-faq-q">How does the online compiler execute code?</summary>
        <div class="comp-faq-a">
          <p>We use <a href="https://github.com/engineer-man/piston" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Piston</a>, an open-source code execution engine that runs your code in isolated containers. Your code never runs on our main server. It executes in a sandboxed environment.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="comp-faq-item">
        <summary class="comp-faq-q">Which programming languages are supported?</summary>
        <div class="comp-faq-a">
          <p>We support 19 languages: Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, C++, C, C#, Go, Rust, Ruby, PHP, Swift, Kotlin, Scala, R, Perl, Lua, Bash, and SQL (SQLite). Each language runs a specific pinned version for consistency.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="comp-faq-item">
        <summary class="comp-faq-q">Is there a time limit on code execution?</summary>
        <div class="comp-faq-a">
          <p>Yes, each execution has a 30-second timeout. This prevents infinite loops from blocking resources. If your code exceeds this limit, you will receive a timeout error.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="comp-faq-item">
        <summary class="comp-faq-q">Can I provide input to my program?</summary>
        <div class="comp-faq-a">
          <p>Yes! Click the STDIN button (book icon) in the editor toolbar to open the standard input panel. Type your input there and it will be passed to your program when it runs.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="comp-faq-item">
        <summary class="comp-faq-q">Is my code stored or shared anywhere?</summary>
        <div class="comp-faq-a">
          <p>No. Your code is sent to the execution engine to run and the output is returned to you. We do not store, log, or share your code. Code is auto-saved to your browser's localStorage only.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="comp-faq-item">
        <summary class="comp-faq-q">Does the editor support syntax highlighting?</summary>
        <div class="comp-faq-a">
          <p>Yes! We use CodeMirror 5 with full syntax highlighting for all 19 languages, including bracket matching, auto-indent, code folding, and dark/light theme support.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="comp-faq-item">
        <summary class="comp-faq-q">What is the maximum code size I can run?</summary>
        <div class="comp-faq-a">
          <p>The maximum code size is 64 KB (65,536 characters) and standard input is limited to 16 KB. Output is limited to 100 KB.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

